.SH NAME
WebGL2RenderingContext.invalidateFramebuffer \- WebGL2RenderingContext:
invalidateFramebuffer() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGL2RenderingContext.invalidateFramebuffer()\f[B]\f[R]
method of the WebGL 2 API invalidates the contents of attachments in a
framebuffer.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
invalidateFramebuffer(target, attachments)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]target\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the binding point (target).
Possible values:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]gl.FRAMEBUFFER\f[R]
Collection buffer data storage of color, alpha, depth and stencil
buffers used to render an image.
.TP
\f[B]gl.DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER\f[R]
Equivalent to \f[CR]gl.FRAMEBUFFER\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]gl.READ_FRAMEBUFFER\f[R]
Used as a source for reading operations.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]attachments\f[R]
An \f[CR]Array\f[R] of \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the attachment
points to invalidate.
Possible values:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]gl.COLOR_ATTACHMENT{0\-15}\f[R]
Invalidates one of the framebuffer\[cq]s color buffers.
.TP
\f[B]gl.DEPTH_ATTACHMENT\f[R]
Invalidates the framebuffer\[cq]s depth buffer.
.TP
\f[B]gl.STENCIL_ATTACHMENT\f[R]
Invalidates the framebuffer\[cq]s stencil buffer.
.TP
\f[B]gl.DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT\f[R]
Invalidates both the framebuffer\[cq]s depth and stencil buffer.
.RE
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
gl.invalidateFramebuffer(gl.READ_FRAMEBUFFER, [
  gl.COLOR_ATTACHMENT0,
  gl.COLOR_ATTACHMENT1,
]);
.EE
